    <string name="faq_content">
    <b>Q: Why can\'t the app find my Bluetooth device?</b>\n
    A: Please make sure your Bluetooth device is turned on, has sufficient battery, and is in discoverable mode. Also, please check if the app has been granted the necessary Bluetooth and Location permissions. The location permission must be set to \"Allow all the time\".\n\n

    <b>Q: What should I do if data synchronization fails?</b>\n
    A: Please check if your network connection is stable. You can try restarting the app or disconnecting and reconnecting the Bluetooth device. If the problem persists, please check if the server address on the settings page is configured correctly.\n\n

    <b>Q: What should I do if the app stops working in the background?</b>\n
    A: To ensure the app continues to run in the background, you may need to set this app to \"Unrestricted\" or \"Allow background activity\" in your phone\'s battery optimization settings. The settings path may vary for different phone brands. It is known that making a WeChat voice call can reawaken the background service, which has a high probability of restoring the reporting service for a period of time. This issue cannot be completely resolved due to system background limitations.\n\n
    </string>
